title: Cuban Fisherman
desc: This man lived in Tampa, Florida for over 30 years and was a devoted fan of Lebron James, had his life forever changed when an intruder broke into his home one night. He had to use a gun to protect himself and killed the intruder. However, because he did not have proper ID, he was ultimately repatriated back to Cuba, where he now lives as a fisherman in the small town of Matanzas.

title: Living in an Unfinished House
desc: Iván's friend lives in this unfinished house, the brick walls are bare and unpainted, wooden planks everywhere, one side even missing a wall and a blanket has been put on to cover it up.

title: Living in an Unfinished House
desc: Iván's friend, even living in an unfinished house, happily sits on the only sofa in the house and smokes, also emphasizes that he has a phone - a rather rare item for Cubans.

title: The backyard of Iván's friend
desc: In contrast to the house, the backyard has been planted with plenty of vegetables and livestocks, there is even a tall coconut tree. They are preparing a fresh coconut drink for me.

title: Not Abandoned Basketball Court
desc: Viewed from the roof of the house of Iván's friend. This is the basketball court of a school.

title: F*CK YOU YOU F*CKIN' F*CK
desc: I returned to New York City again in 2022 to capture photographs because I am always fascinated by the streets of New York. While walking down 7th Avenue on my way to the hotel, I saw this shirt hanging outside a souvenir shop and thought it could be a great element to my photo. I stopped to compose the shot and as I was doing so, a man walked gracefully past me. Immediately I knew this was the moment, so I pressed the shutter.
